commitResults.messageBody:
Occurred when performing NotebookTest loadFromFile_corruptedLine_throws().
Scanner not closed when parseLine throws, leaving file handle open so JUnit cannot delete temp dir on Windows.
Fix: use try-with-resources and rethrow FileSystemException.

commitResults.messageTitle: Add GpaEntry, GpaList, GpaInputException classes. astra.gpa.GpaEntry: subject (uppercase, single token), grade (uppercase, validated), mc (non-negative int). astra.gpa.GpaList: holds entries, computes GPA excluding S/U. astra.exception.GpaInputException: handle invalid inputs specifically for gpa.

Enhanced Notebook.java for GPA persistance. Notebook GPA persistence: Reads/writes GPA entries in data/gpa.txt (pipe format: GPA | SUBJECT | GRADE | MC) and data/gpa.csv (Subject,Grade,MC). Loading happens on Notebook construction so GPA entries persist across runs.

Enhanced parser to handle GPA related user inputs into commands. add gpa <subject> <grade> <mc> → AddGpaCommand</subject></grade></mc> list gpa → ListGpaCommand delete gpa <index> → DeleteGpaCommand</index> gpa → ComputeGpaCommand Existing list remains for activities; list gpa is specific for GPA.
Update help text for GPA tracker.

Add all 4 GPA commands. AddGpaCommand: adds subject with grade and mc count to GPA List, with input checks. ComputeGpaCommand: calls computeGPA() and returns a String with current GPA. DeleteGpaCommand: removes a GPA entry based on index in GPA list. ListGpaCommand: returns GPA List which contains subject,grade,mc.

Add unit tests for add/list/gpa/delete flows for GPA tracking. Covers: - adding entries (case-insensitivity and mc parsing with/without mc), - listing entries, - GPA computation (correctly excludes S/U), - deletion by index, and - invalid grade error handling.
Update README and user guides for GPA tracker.
